      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) are directly linked to the regulatory decision question regarding structural adequacy of the pedicle screw construct.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary ASTM F1717 acceptance metrics used by FDA for 510(k) clearance of pedicle screw systems. Force at 40 mm displacement is a secondary ASTM F1717 metric. All three QoIs are directly relevant to the regulatory decision. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
